definition: to insert/stick in/pierce/to take part in/to interfere/to interpose

sentences.chinese: 冰镐安全抱膝客场插槽。

sentences.english: Changed Inventory to show slot quantity permanently.
sentences.chinese: 更改库存以永久显示插槽数量。

sentences.english: Then comes the delicate phase of inserting into designated slots in a cardboard holder for storage.
sentences.chinese: 最后仔细地插入存放在柜里特定的插槽中，储存待用。

sentences.english: Maximum thermal dissipation of the slot in Milliwatts.
sentences.chinese: 以毫瓦表示的插槽的最大温度散发。

sentences.english: Why no SD card slot—or USB, for that matter?
sentences.chinese: 而且，为什么没有SD卡插槽或USB接口？

sentences.english: Do you think Socketed Items will have an impact?
sentences.chinese: 你认为插槽的物品有效果么？

sentences.english: The slot includes a feature game that is triggered by disp…
sentences.chinese: 医疗疯子是医生和护士的主题插槽游戏。

sentences.english: Jagged Deep Peridot Matches a Yellow or Blue Socket.
sentences.chinese: 裂纹翠榄石对应黄色或蓝色插槽。

sentences.english: Only the slots associated with iterators that are actually dereferenced will be invoked.
sentences.chinese: 仅有实际解引用的迭代器所关联的插槽才会被调用。

sentences.english: Moreover, the pieces slot neatly into one another without visible joints nor decorative flourishes.
sentences.chinese: 此外，整齐地相互件插槽无明显接缝，也不装饰盛行。

sentences.english: Slot-level partitioning of physical devices is also supported.
sentences.chinese: 同时还支持物理设备的插槽级分区。

sentences.english: Thus no mutexes are held by the signal while a slot is executing.
sentences.chinese: 因此，当插槽执行时，信号并没有持有互斥体。

sentences.english: When planning your deployments, determine your socket size first.
sentences.chinese: 当规划部署时，首先要决定您的插槽数。

sentences.english: The exchange plans to doublethenumber of slots to meet demand.
sentences.chinese: 为满足需求，此交易所打算将插槽的数量增加一倍。

sentences.english: Maximum length of an adapter card that can be inserted into the slot, in inches.
sentences.chinese: 可插入插槽的适配卡以英寸表示的最大长度。
